ingredients.name: brominated vegetable oil
ingredients.description: Brominated vegetable oil is common in sports drinks and sodas. There are concerns that it could be harmful, particularly because it has been shown to accumulate in the body. BVO is prohibited as a food additive in the European Union.

ingredients.name: food color
ingredients.description: Color additives are tricky - both colors that we might perceive as natural (e.g. fruit juice and turmeric) and artificial colors (e.g. Red 3) might turn up on a food label under "artifical color" or "color added." This makes it difficult to know how safe these colorings are, since you do not know exactly what you are consuming. The FDA is wise not to make a distinction, however, because the process of extracting natural colors is far from natural and these substances are not necessarily safer!

orders.title: Bakery On Main Fiber Power Cinnamon Raisin Granola, 12 Oz
orders.description:
We make people happy.
It all started in the small bakery of a natural foods market on main street in Glastonbury, Connecticut. I listened to my celiac customers concerns about the taste of many of the gluten free options available to them, and thought that no one should have to suffer because of a food allergy or other special dietary need. And so my mission became to create products that would make my customers happy.
Today, that mission has expanded to not only make our customers happy with great-tasting gluten free products, but spreading a little bit of happiness to everyone we meet and work with. I'd also like to encourage you to think about the things that make you happy, and to do something to make yourself, a family member, a friend or even a complete stranger happy.
Now our bakery is bigger, but we still bake in small batches. We hope you love our products as much as we love creating them for you.
Thank you!
Michael Smulders Founder.
Happy celiacs:
When you purchase Bakery On Main products, you are helping to fund celiac research and awareness efforts.
Happy athletes:
Bakery On Main products help fuel amateur and professional athletes.
Non GMO product.
Happiness guaranteed:
If you are not happy with this product, simply return the unused portion for a no-questions-asked refund.
Happy taste buds:
Check out our other great products at bakeryonmain.com.
Questions, comments? 888.533.8118.

ingredients.name: spices
ingredients.description: "Spice" can refer to any number of spices. If you are allergic to a spice, you will need to call the manufacturer to find out which spices are included. Things like wheat and sugar have to be listed separately, so "spice" is safe for gluten free diets.

ingredients.name: natural flavors
ingredients.description: The term "natural flavors" can hide a lot of gross sources of flavor, such as the notorious castoreum from the anal sacs of beavers. Of course, this does not mean these flavorings are harmful, but since you cannot really be sure of what you are getting, it is wise to be cautious.

ingredients.name: inulin
ingredients.description: Inulin is safe, but consuming large amounts may cause gastrointestinal discomfort.

favoriteRecipes.title: Tuna Mexi Melts
favoriteRecipes.summary: Tuna Mexi Melts might be just the main course you are searching for. One serving contains 700 calories, 41g of protein, and 40g of fat. This pescatarian recipe serves 6 and costs $2.7 per serving. 9 people have made this recipe and would make it again. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 45 minutes. If you have bread, juice of lime, jalapeno, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the sour cream you could follow this main course with the Sour Cream Apple Pie as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 77%. This score is good. Try Homemade Mexi-Melts, Seared Ahi Tuna Sea Steak over Mexi-Asian Salsa, and Tuna Melts for similar recipes.
